  <p>6 July 2021</p>
  <h2 class="govuk-heading-m">How to format content</h2>
  <p>MoJ Forms uses something called markdown to let you add formatting to content. Markdown is a way of adding formatting to plain text using basic symbols and patterns. With</p>
  <p>markdown, you can add headings, links, lists, tables and more. For example, to create a</p>
  <p>bulleted list, you start each item with an asterisk (*).&nbsp;</p>
  <p>You can use markdown in any content area, which you will find on content pages, as well as the start page, confirmation page and several other templates.</p>
  <p>The userguide includes a selection of the most common markdown features to use in your forms.</p>
